divs: sighting detailsstar gazing for about 45 minutes starting about 7:45 pm. i saw a meteor west to north, one southeast to northwest. i saw a sattelite south to north and one southeast to northwest. i was focusing on big dipper and north star when 3 relatively dim lights appeared about directly overhead and went straight north and disappeared. appeared very high up and uniform inseparation during flight. they were about 2\3 the brightness of the north star.
